Text.string: Oh, boy. Have I got a job for you!
Help me build a new friend!
Fine. Good enough.
This is gonna be the fastest bot on the planet!
Give him crazy sword hands, too! I need swords.
Sword hands?! How we gonna high-five?
Agreed. Let's use oversphere death lasers instead! Pew pew, baby.
No combat bot! My new friend will roast tasty marshmallows for us! Get some flamethrowers!
Where would we even GET marshmallows? With an acid tank, our new centurion could melt our foes!
I guess that'll work for cleaning up the lab. Less work for me! Fine, acid tank it is.
Something about you agreeing with me is deeply unsettling.
Last thing, we'll need an AI chip for the new bot. Perhaps we can reprogram a Maliwan mech AI?
I'm stuck on this rock with a Grumpy Gus, who shall remain nameless. So I want a new robot friend. To build one, we're gonna need some parts! Go borrow some of Maliwan's stuff!
I dunno, that sounds pretty dangerous. Maybe something easier to control, like an oversphere AI?
Enough! I'll find a damn AI chip on my own!
I'm tired of your bickering! Rgh. Leave this to me. I'll find a bloody AI chip.
Enough of your squabbles. I will find an AI chip on my own.
Oi, that's enough outta you two. I'll find an AI chip on my own.
There it is! Great work, Vault Hunter!
They don't need you patting them on the back every five seconds, Sparrow. Calm your bits.
Just trying to be supportive, unlike SOME bot around here. Now, Vault Hunter—come back and let's put it all together!
We've got the bot frame set up over here. Install those parts you got!
Just slap 'em in there, Vault Hunter.
We'll get our new friend up and running in no time!
Friend? I think he'll hate you. Just, like, automatically.
Wow. Rude.
I suppose we could use an extra pair of hands, since Sparrow barely carries his weight around here.
Now, flip on the power!
It's... FUNCTIONAL! Hahahaha! And for the final step: install the AI chip you found and bring him to life!
AAAAGH! AGHHHH! AGAGAAAAAGH!
Uh oh...
KILL ME! MY EXISTENCE IS PAIN!
Ohhh, crap! It's a freakin' monster!
As much as I hate to agree with my colleague here, it does appear that this horrid creation requires a mercy killing.
KILL ME!
I can't feel my ANYTHING!
I CAME BACK WRONG!
Hey! Not nice. Besides, I'm here for moral support!
PAAAAIN!
This is all your fault, Grouse! I just wanted a new friend!
No, it's YOUR fault. You never take anything seriously and you probably messed up the frame somehow.
Thank... you...
Well that didn't go... super great. But, what matters is we tried.
Yes. Tried and failed.
Thank you for trying to help!
Even if it was a colossal failure. Which it was.
At least we didn't get destroyed by our own creation! Wouldn't that have been tragic?
Well, Typhon put ME in charge of security, and I say we need a combat bot to protect us! One with heavy armor to deflect our enemies' assaults.
We don't need a combat bot, we need a cool friend who can fly around and do sweet tricks!
Maneuverability IS key for battle, as well as “sweet tricks”. How about oversphere thrusters?
No! Jetpacks!
Quiet. Vault Hunter, acquire some flash trooper backpacks.
